        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "SKS World School - Sector 137"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Sheel Pant"
          },
          "datePublished": "2024-10-23",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Few good teachers have already left the school, and the relievers are not so competent.\n\nTeachers are speaking Hindi with the students; hence, students are reluctant to communicate or converse in English. Except for Minakshee Ma’am, the staff in reception are very poor in communication and the ability of conveyancing is very poor.\n\nTeacher of nursery class, Mrs. Sangeeta, fails to deal with young kids. It has been observed that she became irritated and also remained busy on her mobile phone, leaving young people under the supervision of Didi. Didi in the class speaks very harsh language with the kids. They never insist young kids finish their meals.\n\nGetting a reply to an email from the school authority is a thousand-dollar question,  maybe the school authority is not qualified enough to write an email.\n\nThe principal of the school is most unimpressive. Her administrative ability is below expectations.\n\nThe SKS School authority is good, but they are ignoring Sector 137 school. My suggestion to all, kindly please verify all aspects before getting admission to your kids.\n\nJai Hind",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
